5000|$|<b>Volenti</b> non fit iniuria (or injuria) (Latin: [...] "to {{a willing}} person, injury is not done") {{is a common}} law {{doctrine}} which states that if someone willingly places themselves {{in a position where}} harm might result, knowing that some degree of harm might result, they are not able to bring a claim against the other party in tort or delict. <b>Volenti</b> only applies to the risk which a reasonable person would consider them as having assumed by their actions; thus a boxer consents to being hit, and to the injuries that might be expected from being hit, but does not consent to (for example) his opponent striking him with an iron bar, or punching him outside the usual terms of boxing. <b>Volenti</b> is also known as a [...] "voluntary assumption of risk." ...|$|E
