50|$|In law, volens is a {{state of}} mind, {{referring}} to voluntary acceptance of a specific risk. It is usually pleaded by way of defence, and often employs the legal Latin <b>volenti</b> non fit injuria. The term volens itself is often used in contradistinction to the terms sciens (meaning mere knowledge of the risk, without any voluntary assumption of it).|$|E
