50|$|In {{contract}} law, many clauses in contracts {{which at}} first {{appear to be}} exemption clauses relating to personal injury (which are in many countries invalid by law) are in fact phrased so as {{to demonstrate that the}} person signing the contract was aware of and voluntarily accepted the risk of personal injury, which may then subsequently establish a successful <b>volenti</b> defence.|$|E
